gomodel:SYNGO_2868  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"UPS46 synaptic distribution and developmental expression\"\n- \" In 2-week-old cultured rat hippocampal neurons, USP46 was labeled with specific antibodies together with AMPAR GluA1 subunits, or with a postsynaptic marker protein PSD-95. USP46 showed a punctate distribution pattern and was mostly co-localized with GluA1 or PSD95, indicating synaptic localization (Fig. 1a and b).\"\n- \"Consistent with immunostaining results, western blots revealed that, similar to the known synaptic proteins including GluA1 and PSD95, USP46 was enriched in the synaptosomal P2 fractions compared with the lysates (Fig. 1c).\". Experimental description: - \"Primary cultured cortical and hippocampal neurons were prepared from embryonic day 18 rat embryos as previously described (Hou et al. 2008).\"\n- \"Cortical tissue dissected from adult rat brains was ....\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-16" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2868" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

